Even or Odd
Pseudo code:
Start
Declare X
Input X =  ”enter the number:”
If X < 0 then 
         Print “negative numbers can be even or odd”
Else If X % 2 == 0 then
       Print   X+” is a Even Number”
Else
       Print   X +” is a Odd Number”
End
 
Largest Number in Three numbers
      Pseudo Code :
Start
Declare X , Y , Z
Input X =”enter the first Number:”
Input Y =” enter the second Number:”
Input Z =” enter the Third Number:”
If X==Y AND Y==Z then 
              Print All values are equal
Else if (X > Y AND X > Z ) then 
                  Print   X + “is largest Number”
else if ( Y > X AND Y > Z ) then 
                 Print   Y + “is largest Number”
else 
                 Print   Z + “ is largest Number”
End
 
Sum of Numbers from 1 to N
     Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare N, Sum = 0
Input N =”enter the Number”
If N > 0 then
For i = 1 to N increment by 1
Sum = Sum + i
Print Sum
Else
          Print “ Invalid Input”
End
                
Factorial of a Number
Pseudo code :
Start
Declare N, Fact = 1
Input N =”enter the Number”
If N >0 then
For  i =1 to N increment by 1
Fact = Fact * i
Print Fact
Else 
        Negative numbers can’t exists
End
Check Prime Number
   Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare Num , Count =0
Input Num =”enter the Number”
If Num >1 then
For i =2 to Num-1 increment by 1
If Num % i ==0 then 
              Count ++
If Count == 0 then 
         Print   Num +”is a Prime “
Else
        Print   Num +”is not a Prime”
Else
        Print “Number must greater than 1”
End
 
Print Multiplication Table
    Pseudo code:
Start
Declare Num
Input Num = ”enter the Number for multiplication table”
If Num >=1 then
For i =1 to 10 increment by 1
Print Num +”x”+ i +”=” Num*i
Else 
         Print “Invalid Input”
End
 
Reverse a Number
Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare Num,Rev =0,digit
Input Num =”enter the minimum two digit  number which is going to be reversed”
If Num > 0 then
While Num != 0 
       Digit = Num % 10 
      Rev = Rev * 10 + digit
     Num = Num //10
Print Rev
Else
       Print “Invalid Input”
End
 
Count Digits in a Number
         Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare Num, Count =0
Input Num =”enter the Number”
If Num == 0 then 
                Count = 1
Else
         Num = absolute value of Num
While Num != 0
              Num = Num //10
              Count ++
Print “the no of digits in a number”+ Count
End
 
Fibonacci Series
       Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare n,Num1 = 0,Num2=1,Num3
Input n =”enter the range of a number”
Print Num1 , Num2
If n >2 then
For  i =2 to n increment by 1
Num3 = Num1 + Num2
Print Num3
Num1 = Num2
Num2 = Num3
Else
              Exist
End
 
Check Palindrome Number
        Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare Num,Rev =0,Digit,OriginalNum.
Input Num =”enter the number which is going to be reversed”
Set OriginalNum = num
While Num != 0
       Digit = Num % 10
      Rev = Rev * 10 + digit
     Num = Num //10
If Rev == OriginalNum then 
               Print “the number is palindrome”+OriginalNum
Else
           Print “the number is not a Palindrome”+ OriginalNum
End
 
Sum of Even Numbers
             Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare N, Sum =0
Input N = “enter the range “
If N > 0 then
For i=1 to N increment by 1
If i % 2 == 0 then
        Sum = Sum + i
Print Sum
Else 
         Print “Invalid Input”
End
 
Grade Calculator
Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare Marks, Grade =””
Input Marks= ”enter the marks”
If Marks > 0 AND Marks <=100 then
  If Marks >=90 AND Marks <=100  then 
                                Grade=”A”
 Else if Marks >= 80 AND Marks <=89  then 
                              Grade =”B”
 Else if Marks >= 70 AND Marks <= 79 then 
                               Grade =”C”
 Else if Marks >= 60 AND Marks <= 69 then 
                                Grade = “D”
 Else if Marks < 60
                               Grade =”F”
                  Else 
         Print “invalid input”
 
Print Grade.
End
 
Print Pattern
              Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare Num,
Input Num =”enter the Number”
If Num >0 then
For i =0 to Num increment by 1
          For j=0  to i  increment by 1 
                  Print “*”
                 Print  new line
Else 
           Exist
End     
         Simple Calculator 
               Pseudo Code:
Start
Declare num1 , num2 , op
Input num1 = “enter the first number:”
Input num2 =”enter the  second number:”
Input op = “enter the operator “
If op =”+” then 
        print  num1 + num2
else if op =”-“
        print num1 – num2
else if op =”*”
       print num1* num2
else if op =”/”
        if  num2 != 0  then 
                    print num1/ num2 
       Else 
                   Print “Cannot divide by zero”
Else 
               Print “invalid operator”
 
